<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 py-16">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white text-center mb-10">Frequently asked questions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Will there ever be a paid plan?</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Enzyme is MIT licensed open-source software. The code is free and always will be. If we offer paid services in the future, they would be things like managed hosting — the self-hosted version will remain free.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">What does self-hosting cost?</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Just the cost of a server. Enzyme runs on a single $5/month VPS. There are no license fees, no per-seat charges, and no feature gates.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Is Enzyme Cloud suitable for production use?</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Enzyme Cloud is great for small teams. For larger teams or stricter data requirements, we recommend self-hosting so you have full control over your data, backups, and uptime.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Are there any feature differences?</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">No. Enzyme Cloud runs the exact same code as the self-hosted version. Every feature is available everywhere. Cloud workspaces have a 100 MB file storage limit.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

